<div class="newsItem">
<a name="bethelight"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">Be the Light - Message From Principal Gee</div>
	<div class="newsbody">
<p class="">Hello Mingus Families:</p>
<p class="">As a special symbol of hope and solidarity for our Mingus seniors, Mingus Union High School will be participating in the "Be the Light" movement to honor our graduating class. Every Friday night, beginning April 17 through May 22, the Mingus football stadium lights will be turned on at 8:20 p.m. (20:20 military time) and left on for 20 minutes and 20 seconds. This is a tribute to our Mingus graduating class of 2020 and we ask that our Mingus families and community members turn on their porch lights during this time to honor our seniors as well. We may be physically separated, but we are emotionally connected and we hope that this will give our seniors reason to smile and feel comforted knowing their school and community is thinking about them.</p>
<ul><li class="">April 17 to May 22, 2020 - Be the Light 8:20 p.m. for 20 minutes and 20 seconds.</li></ul>
<p></p>
</div>
